      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Revised Draft</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">3/17/2026</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">512 W 158th St #2 New York, New York 10032</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">david</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="4" Style=""> </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">@</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="4" Style=""> </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">flavorpictures</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">.</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">com</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">616 818 5413</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Logline</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">In a last-ditch effort to reinvent herself, a struggling educator must win the host role in the beloved children’s tv series </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">STARPOWER</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">!, only to face the original host’s legacy and a public resistant to inclusivity.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Episode</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Ray, a struggling educator who finds out her childhood show, </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Stardust</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">, is being revived without its original host, leads her on a quest to secure a role for herself.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Plot Summary</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">In 2001, four-year-old Trini “Ray” Reyes is a fan of </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Stardust</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">, an educational show hosted by the energetic Clay. Over the following years, Ray uses the show’s lessons to help her younger brother, Kwan, cope with difficult childhood events, such as a tornado and their parents' foreclosure.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">By 2025, Ray’s theatre career ends in disaster after accidentally burning down a puppet show and a birthday party. Blacklisted, she finds a spark of hope in a viral video from her childhood hero, Clay, returning to encourage former viewers to keep looking up.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Seeking a fresh start, Ray visits Kwan at Michigan State University, where she learns that the show's creator, River Matthews, is appearing at an arts fair. There, Ray attempts to pitch herself as a collaborator, but River dismisses her.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Ray soon meets the show’s co-creator, Skye Park, who invites her to dinner with River. Ray gifts them a vintage walkie-talkie from the show, only to secretly record their conversation where Ray discovers a revival has been greenlit. But the creators plan to bypass auditions and hire Ray’s polished rival, Ms. Aurora.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Kwan reveals he has been in contact with the original host, Billy Clayton Dubois, and drives Ray to his apartment in Brooklyn. When Ray finally meets her childhood hero and asks for his help to save Stardust, a disheveled and weary Clay looks into her camera and asks, "Do I look like I care?"</Text>
      </Paragraph>
    </Content>
    <TextState Scaling="100" Selection="1122,1122" ShowInvisibles="No"/>
  </TitlePage>

